analysis: The agent failed to match the expected parameter casing: it used capitalized beneficiary names ("User", "Sister") and "Grandchild" instead of the required lowercase ("user", "sister", "grandchild"), leading to a mismatch with the evaluator's strict parameter matching.

The agent incorrectly formatted the "time_frame" parameter using full datetime strings instead of the required "YYYY-MM-DD" date-only format, causing the function call to not match the expected schema.

The agent incorrectly specified the "sourceId" as "techdataapi" instead of the required "1", causing a parameter mismatch that prevented proper function call recognition by the evaluator. All other fields matched as expected.

The model incorrectly formatted the timestamps in the function arguments by including a trailing "Z" (indicating UTC) instead of the expected format without it, causing the function call not to match the required schema.

The agent made two separate function calls instead of combining both sslTlsManagement and dataAtRestEncryption parameters into a single WebSecurity_EncryptionManager call as required by the tool's expected usage.

The agent used the wrong campaign title, set the duration year to 2024 instead of 2023, and limited the ageRange max to 30 instead of the expected 35, resulting in parameter mismatches with the expected function call.

The agent failed to invoke the required function and instead requested additional information from the user, despite having sufficient details in the prompt to call the SpeciesClassifier_identifyFeatures tool as expected.

The agent's function call omitted required fields: the "historical" flag and unique "source_id" values for each traffic source in "traffic_data", which resulted in a mismatch with the expected structured function parameters.

The agent used the internal restaurant_id "luigis_italian_restaurant" instead of the required display name "Luigi's Italian Restaurant" for the restaurant_id parameter, causing a mismatch with the expected function call inputs.

The agent used an incorrect or non-matching parameter value for the "imageData" argument instead of passing the user-provided base64 string as required, resulting in no match with the expected function call.
The agent omitted the "Free Play" activity from the routineDetails in the function call, failing to include all user-specified activities in the morning routine as required.

The model failed to match the function call format by capitalizing "Green Tea" instead of "green tea" in the "teaName" parameter, causing the evaluator to not recognize it as equivalent to the expected function call.
The agent output an extra closing brace in the tool call JSON, resulting in invalid JSON that could not be parsed. This syntax error prevented the function from being called as expected.

The agent included an extra "readingLevel" field in the "userProfile" argument, which was not expected; this mismatch in parameters caused the function call to not match the expected schema, leading to evaluation failure.

The agent output extraneous XML-like tags ("<tool_call>...</tool_call>") and included an extra closing brace in the JSON, resulting in invalid, unparsable tool call output instead of the required raw JSON object.

The agent placed the vibration_patterns parameter at the top level of the function arguments instead of nesting it inside app_details as required by the expected API schema, resulting in a parameter structure mismatch.

The agent incorrectly set the end time of the timeWindow parameter to "2020-03-02T23:59:59" instead of the expected "2020-03-02T23:59:00", resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected function call.

The agent outputted the tool call as raw JSON wrapped inside non-standard <tool_call> XML tags, resulting in invalid and unparsable JSON due to trailing characters after the closing brace. The output format did not match the expected structured tool call format.

The agent included an unsupported "fontWeight" parameter in the function call, which does not match the available function's expected parameters. Only "fontFamily" should have been provided in "typographyPreferences".

The agent included an extra "process_info" field with an empty list in the "details" object, causing the function call's parameters to not match the expected schema and resulting in evaluation failure.

The agent used "Great Wall - Beijing Segment" as the siteId instead of the correct "Great Wall Beijing". This mismatch caused the function call to not match the expected parameters, leading to the failure.
